REST ENDPOINTS


FETCH ALL --> 	GET localhost:8080/api/employees

FETCH Id -->  	GET localhost:8080/api/employees/{id}     #provide id in URI without {}

CREATE --> 		POST localhost:8080/api/employees      #provide json obj in Request body 

UPDATE --> 		PUT localhost:8080/api/employees/{id} 	#provide id in URI without {} & json obj in Request body

DELETE -->		DELETE localhost:8080/api/employees/{id} #provide id in URI without {}

json example
{
        "firstName": "Christina",
        "lastName": "D'souza",
        "email": "Christina@icloud.com"
}


REST QUERY ENDPOINTS

Search by First Name --> 
GET localhost:8080/api/employees/queryFirst?Fname={fn}		#provide first name(fn) in URI without {}

Search by Last Name -->
GET localhost:8080/api/employees/queryLast?Lname={ln}		#provide last name(ln) in URI without {}

Search by Email -->
GET localhost:8080/api/employees/queryEmail?Email={e}		#provide email(e) in URI without {}

Search by First and Last Name -->
GET localhost:8080/api/employees/queryFirstLast?Fname={fn}&Lname={ln}  #provide fn and ln in URI without {}






